description.p:
Preferably, the component is chosen from the following elements: a pump; a level gauge; a temperature sensor; a quality sensor; a pressure sensor and a pressure regulator. These elements each have an active role in the additive storage and/or injection system, and the fact of integrating them into a mounting plate that is “submerged” (that is to say, always in the presence of the additive, as long as the tank is not empty) has specific advantages:


for the level gauge: the low point is better defined and therefore the measurement is less affected by deformations of the tank;

for the sensors of temperature, quality or other characteristic(s) of the additive: makes it possible to easily locate it in the critical zone for feeding to the injection system.
